messages.message: @Xindi Xu apologies for the delayed response -- fwict 23.01 recently was updated to use the overlay-based python dependencies in pre-merge (@Cody Boggs any idea when this got updated?). 23.07 is already utilizing mypy 0.812 and was updated to fix broken types in https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/53761, so it sounds like something recently changed which should not have passed in pre-merge

:face_with_raised_eyebrow: Interesting
I didn't think I had pushed it back that far, will look
I didn't either and could have swore we only backported through 23.04 :sweat_smile:

I don't ever remember this happening, but looks like it got backported (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/release-23.01.0/tools/releasetools/jenkins/pipelines/ci-tests.groovy) ~6 months ago, I'm very surprised we haven't seen more issues like this since

I'll have a PR up shortly to ensure the correct version of mypy is used on 23.01
Yea I'm kinda lost on why this suddenly broke :confused_dog:
haha yeah, I'm sorry I didn't remember backporting that far :face_palm:
What about this PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/55069) against 23.07? There's only 1 unrelated type error. Is this related to the mypy version mismatch?

I'm still unsure why that's breaking, but I suspect it's likely due to some change not failing pre merge checks like it's supposed to -- I can put a pr up to fix that code as well, but if you're comfortable adding it to your backport you'll probably get unblocked faster :slightly_smiling_face:
Got it! I can add the fix to my PR. :ty:
tyty! will have the 23.01 fix up shortly :slightly_smiling_face:

<!subteam^S038TM462UX> / @Xindi Xu the checks take a long time (actually about to work on a pr to backport some of the pre-merge optimizations), but I tested https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/55192  with the changes from https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/55071 and all the type checks passed :smile: -- would appreciate a review whenever someone has time
